		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How come everyone here likes CompactFlash so much when it appears that the much more common (and cheaper!) SD cards don't look so hard to work with? The <a href="http://harmony.atariage.com/" class="postlink">Harmony Cartridge</a> (the Atari 2600 equivalent to the PowerPak) for example, uses SD cards for storage.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


